    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "[cppyy](https://cppyy.readthedocs.io/en/latest/) has all the information available that is needed for generating .pxd declaration files from C/C++ .h header files. Use it.\r\n\r\n(Also see https://github.com/cython/cython/wiki/AutoPxd for the time being.)",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Here is another one I'm using for C at the moment:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/gabrieldemarmiesse/python-autopxd2/\r\n\r\nI've been patching up some corner cases that it didn't yet cover, but it looks like the best-in-class for automatic .pyx generation that exists already. No C++ though. Could be a good reference for implementing more general code generation, or if nothing covering c++ eventuates, cython might consider including autopxd(2) under the Cython banner.",
